<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 5000, 9000 Series Without Lowered heater Box - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        THERMOSTATIC TEMPERATURE CONTROL SWITCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601506" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>THERMOSTATIC TEMPERATURE CONTROL SWITCH</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch and A/C lever are off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the screws securing the passenger seat and the Blend-Air housing cover plate.
                    Remove the seat and cover from the cab.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect wiring connectors from the thermostatic control switch (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601517">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1601517" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1601514B.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Thermostatic Control Switch</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CAPILLARY TUBE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. THERMOSTATIC CONTROL SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. A/C CONTROL CABLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FILTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. EVAPORATOR CORE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before disconnecting wires, take note of the circuit locations to insure correct reassembly.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove thermostatic control switch mounting screws and the switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retainer clip and disconnect the control cable from the switch lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Withdraw the thermostatic control switch capillary tube from the evaporator core.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully insert the end of the capillary tube into the evaporator core (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601517">Figure 17</hotlnk>). Do not insert in the same hole as removed. Insert
                    nearby to provide good contact with the fins.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the control cable to the thermostatic control switch lever and install the
                    retainer clip.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the switch on the bracket and install the switch mounting screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the wiring connectors to the thermostatic control switch. Make sure the
                    connectors are located properly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the operation of the thermostatic control switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the Blend-Air unit cover and the passenger seat.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
